</span>
</span></p><h2>How to Use Honey Mustard Dressing</h2><p>This homemade honey mustard dressing will keep in an airtight container or Mason jar in the fridge for up to a week, so it&#8217;s a great recipe to <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/healthy-meal-prep-ideas/ >meal prep</a> and keep on hand. It&#8217;s versatile, so have fun experimenting with different ways to use it. Here are a few of my favorites:</p><ul><li><strong>As a salad dressing.</strong> Not to state the obvious, but this dressing is delicious on salad! I call for it specifically in my <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/green-bean-salad-recipe/ >green bean salad recipe</a>, but it&#8217;s also fantastic on <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/sweet-potato-salad-recipe/ >this sweet potato salad</a>, <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/broccoli-salad/ >this broccoli salad</a>, <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/kale-salad>this kale salad</a>, <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/chopped-salad/ >this chopped salad</a>, or simple mixed greens.</li><li><strong>With roasted or sautéed veggies.</strong> Drizzle it over <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/roasted-broccoli/ >roasted broccoli</a>, <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/roasted-cauliflower/ >cauliflower</a>, <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/roasted-brussels-sprouts/ >Brussels sprouts</a>, <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/roasted-potatoes/ >potatoes</a>, or <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/sauteed-broccoli/ >sautéed broccoli</a> for a punch of sweet and tangy flavor.</li><li><strong>As a dipping sauce. </strong>Zuzh up <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/baked-sweet-potato-fries/ >sweet potato fries</a> or <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/air-fryer-french-fries/ >air fryer French fries</a> with a side of honey mustard dressing! Or, for a light and healthy snack, serve it with fresh veggies like carrots, celery, or bell peppers for dipping.</li><li><strong>On a grain bowl. </strong>Start with a grain like <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/farro/ >farro</a>, <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/quinoa/ >quinoa</a>, or <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/how-to-cook-brown-rice/ >brown rice</a>, add a protein like <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/roasted-chickpeas/ >roasted chickpeas</a> or <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/tempeh/ >tempeh</a>, and pile in your favorite veggies. Pour the dressing on top to tie it all together!</li></ul><p>How do you like to use honey mustard dressing? Let me know in the comments!</p><p>
